COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1029, L.D. 1571
315 An educational technician certificate issued under this subsection is for the same period
326 and subject to the same renewal standards as specified in subsection 3. State board rules
337 may further govern qualifications for an educational technician certificate issued under this
348 subsection.'
5 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
6 number to read consecutively.
7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that,
99 beginning August 1, 2026, a full-time teacher in a public charter school must hold an
1100 appropriate teaching certificate. The amendment also provides that, beginning August 1,
1111 2026, the Commissioner of Education may reissue an educational technician certificate to
1122 a person who has been receiving a retirement benefit from the State Employee and Teacher
1133 Retirement Program for no more than 3 years and whose lapsed certificate had been in good
1144 standing.
